# Agents reference

Detailed descriptions for all agents (roles, goals, backstory, tools, handoffs) are in **`AGENTS.md`** at the repo root.

- Before adding or changing an agent, read `AGENTS.md` and update it so it stays the single source of truth.
- When deciding which agent should do a task or how they hand off, refer to `AGENTS.md`.
- Keep `AGENTS.md` in sync with code under `agents/` (and any crew assembly in `main.py`).

If the project has no agents yet, create `AGENTS.md` with a template section per agent (name, role, goal, backstory, tools, delegates to / receives from).
